-- CORRECT: Brazil Extends Bonds Tax Break to 6-Year FIDC Funds
-- B y   A r n a l d o   G a l v a o
-- 2013-01-02T22:18:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-02/correct-brazil-extends-bonds-tax-break-to-6-year-fidc-funds.html
(Finance Ministry corrects
information on FIDC tax break released on Dec. 31) Tax exemption
on infrastructure local bonds with minimum 4-year duration is
extended to asset-backed funds with minimum 6-year duration,
called FIDC.
* Rule applies to FIDC funds linked to infrastructure projects
* Tax exemption for foreign investors, Brazilian individual
investors
* Deputy Economic Policy Secretary at the Finance Ministry
Pablo Fonseca tells reporters in Brasilia  To contact the reporter on this story:
